  "description": "High reactivity with moderate memory — the membrane shears on attack but sustains the residual coupling energy for a beat or two. High selectivity means only bright air-band content passes into the colored output. Coupling output rides the sharp-attack sustained-decay shape that makes a snare crack feel like a shockwave. The defining aggressive Osmosis configuration: use when you want the outside world to hit hard and linger.",
